urls.description: This is the second issue of TSB's 33rd season, guaranteed to be a better read than the programme notes. Can I buy it at the ground? As always since 1989, The Square Ball magazine was going to be on sale outside Elland Road, for the big match against Nottingham Forest and their squad of hundreds on Monday 12th September 2022. After the death of Queen Elizabeth II that game has been postponed, so we hope you’ll help us out by getting a copy online, subscribing, or buying one at the next home game against Aston Villa on Sunday 2nd October. Just look out for our windswept but friendly sellers by the Lowfields tunnel, Billy’s Statue, the Kop gates, and anywhere else someone is holding a fanzine in the air, until about fifteen minutes before kick-off. Can I subscribe? Getting the magazine delivered to your home is a very good idea, as it will arrive free of beer stains and torn corners, unless your postie is having a bad morning.
